Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of @water{300} on to boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2}(stalks and all). Cut the top off the @aubergine{1}, halve lengthways and chop into 3cm chunks. Trim the tops from the @green beans{1/2} and chop into thirds.

When the water is boiling, add the @basmati rice{150}. Cook for ~{10%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and leave to rest with the lid on for ~{10%minutes}. The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Put the aubergine on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a generous amount of @black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and slightly crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Add the @cashew nuts{25}. Cook, shaking the pan constantly until the nuts are lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Then place in a #small bowl{} and set aside.

> Watch your nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Turn the heat down to medium and add the @coconut milk{200} and @massaman curry paste{1} to your (now empty) frying pan. Stir to make sure they are combined, then add the mushrooms. Bring to the boil and add the green beans and @peanut butter{1.5}. Stir and turn the heat to low. Gently simmer for ~{10%minutes}. Once the aubergine is cooked, remove from your oven and add to the curry.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and add it to the curry along with three-quarters of the coriander. Add a squeeze of @lime{1/2} juice - taste and add more if you like things zingy! Serve into #bowls{} and garnish with the cashew nuts and remaining coriander. Enjoy!